  "text": "As an example of useful parameter sharing, consider the faithfulness features 1[/p/ → /b/] and 1[/p/ → /r/], which are indicator functions for the appearance of two substitutions for /p/. We would like the model to learn that the former event (a simple voicing change) should be preferred over the latter. In [CITATION_1] , this has to be learned for each branch in the tree. The difficulty is that not all branches will have enough information to learn this preference, meaning that we need to define the model in such a way that it can generalize across languages.",
